article.description: Christian Agnew had 17 points and eight rebounds as North Alabama topped Morehead State 67-57 on Saturday.
article.headline: Agnew lifts North Alabama past Morehead St. 67-57
article.linkText: Agnew lifts North Alabama past Morehead St. 67-57
article.story: FLORENCE, Ala. -- Christian Agnew had 17 points and eight rebounds as North Alabama topped Morehead State 67-57 on Saturday. Payton Youngblood had 16 points for North Alabama (4-4), which earned its fourth consecutive home victory. Jamari Blackmon added 12 points. Mervin James had 12 rebounds for the home team. James Baker had 14 points for the Eagles (4-4), who have now lost four games in a row. Jordan Walker added 12 points. Tyzhaun Claude had seven rebounds. North Alabama plays Troy on the road on Wednesday. Morehead State matches up against IUPUI at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
